    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The style and culture of the colonial Kingdom of New Granada, which existed from the 16th century to the early 19th century and encompassed the territory that is now Colombia, as well as small portions of present-day Venezuela, Panama, and Ecuador. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
